success.question_text: How many cubes of any size can be found in the solid?

stimulus_1.text: The solid is made from small cubes.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

When a solid is made from small cubes many will be hidden from view. Remember to count all the cubes, visible or hidden.

success.question_text: Through how many degrees will the plane turn?

stimulus_2.text:
An air force plane is flying in a north-easterly direction.

It is instructed to change direction and fly in a westerly direction.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A compass rose shows directions to North, East, South and West. In between these directions are North-East, South-East, South-West and North-West.

success.question_text: What is the sum of the lengths of all the edges of the cube?

stimulus_1.text: A cube has sides of length 4 cm.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

A solid can be described by its number of faces, edges and vertices.

stimulus_1.text: The diagram shows a part of a square made up of smaller squares in a chequered pattern.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

When completing a jigsaw question remember to use rotation to change the orientation of the missing piece.

success.question_text: What is the shortest distance that Suzannah must travel?

stimulus_1.text: The diagram shows a map of five towns and the road distances between them.

stimulus_3.text: Suzannah wants to travel from Helena to Turpentine, visiting both Verbena and Pottsville on the way.

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

The shortest distance would be if Suzannah travels from Helena through Malvern to Pottsville, then to Verbena and finally Turpentine.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Don’t rush into answering a question. Take time to think.

stimulus_1.text: The diagram shows a map of five towns and the road distances between them.

stimulus_3.text: Three friends, Samuel, Daniel and Zac, decide to ride their bikes from Verbena to Malvern. They all ride at the same speed. While Daniel rides directly to Malvern, Samuel rides through Helena and Zac rides through both Turpentine and Pottsville. Zac leaves first, ten minutes later Daniel sets off and five minutes after that Samuel leaves Verbena.

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

Without knowing the speed at which they ride it is impossible to determine how long their journeys will take.

There is not enough information to determine who will arrive first.

review_2.column_1_text:
Tip

Don’t forget to look at the options. You need to be aware that you might not be able to find an answer.

choice_4.label: There is not enough information to determine who will arrive first.

success.question_text: To do this, where could Maura start and finish?

stimulus_1.text: The diagram shows a map of five towns and the road distances between them.

stimulus_3.text: Maura wants to prove to her friends that she can begin in one town and travel to all the other towns, along every road, but only travelling along each road once (although she might visit some of the towns more than once).

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

Looking at the map, there are two towns that have an odd number of roads leading from them. These must be the starting and finishing points.

One possible route is:

review_3.column_1_text:
Maura could start at Malvern and finish at Pottsville.

Tip

When determining whether a continuous path can be found through a network, look to see how many vertices are odd. Odd vertices can only be starting or finishing points.

choice_2.label: Start at Malvern and finish at Pottsville

choice_3.label: Start at Helena and finish at Turpentine

choice_4.label: Start at Turpentine and finish at Verbena

stimulus_1.text: Which of the following nets could be folded to make the cube shown?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

To find the arrangements of faces of a cube from its net, first find the faces that will be opposites on the cube.

Tip

Prisms have two identical faces, after which the prism is named, and the other faces are rectangles. Pyramids have a base, after which the pyramid is named, and triangular faces that meet at a point.

success.question_text: What image is seen in the mirror?

stimulus_1.text: This shape is reflected in the mirror. The mirror acts like an axis of symmetry.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

A reflection is like painting a shape on paper and then folding the paper to produce an identical image. A reflection is often described as a flip. When the two shapes are being compared, the fold line is the axis of symmetry.

success.question_text: Which of the following statements is correct?

stimulus_1.text:
Daniel made two identical square pyramids.

He glued the bases together to make one solid.

review_3.column_1_text:
By counting, the solid has eight faces, twelve edges and six vertices.

The correct statement is ‘The solid has eight faces and twelve edges’.

Tip

A solid can be described by its number of faces, edges and vertices.

choice_1.label: The solid has eight faces and twelve edges.

choice_2.label: The solid has ten faces and twelve edges.

choice_3.label: The solid has eight faces and four vertices (corners).

choice_4.label: The solid has twelve edges and five vertices (corners).

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

When paper folding, the number of layers of paper gives the number of repeated cut-out shapes.

stimulus_1.text: Which of the following shows the top view of the shape drawn?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Viewed from the top, the edges of a solid appear as lines and any vertex of the solid (as in the top of a pyramid) will appear as a point.

Tip

Anticlockwise means in the opposite direction to the way in which the hands of a clock turn.

success.question_text: If the distance from Angelford to Brackety is 8 centimetres on the map, how far apart are the two towns actually?

stimulus_2.text: The scale on a map is 1 centimetre represents 40 kilometres.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A map is drawn to scale where lengths on the map represent distances on the ground. e.g. A scale can be expressed in the form of 1:1000 or 1 cm = 10 m, and so on.

success.question_text: What is the view from the right side?

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

Practise by building objects from blocks and looking at the result from all directions.

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

When the card flips over its bottom edge it is turned upside down, but still has the opening in the G on the right side. When the card flips over the right side, it is still upside down but the opening will now be on the left side.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A flip is another name for a reflection.

success.question_text: Which shapes are needed to complete the symmetrical design?

stimulus_1.text: When correctly completed, this design will have half-turn symmetry.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

If a design has half-turn symmetry it looks exactly the same if turned upside down.

success.question_text: What is the actual distance from Azure to Teal?

stimulus_1.text: This is a map of Lake Bluewater.

stimulus_3.text: The actual distance from Skye to Sapphire is 24 kilometres.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A scale must be the same for the whole diagram.
